message.content:
Below is one workable analysis of the picture and a matching “bill of materials” from the block‐dictionary, followed by a suggested build‐order.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  DESCRIPTION OF THE TARGET BUILD
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• Overall there are two separate “towers.”

LEFT TOWER (“vertical sandwich”):
 • 5 layers tall, from top to bottom:
   1) A red arch block (arch facing front).  
   2) A short green rectangular block.  
   3) Two yellow half‐cylinders side by side (forming a full cylinder front‐to‐back).  
   4) Another short green rectangular block.  
   5) A red arch block (arch facing front).  

RIGHT TOWER:
 • Base: two orange cylinders side by side, supporting a horizontal yellow rectangular “bridge.”  
 • Above the “bridge”:  
   – One red arch block (arch on the bottom).  
   – One yellow half‐cylinder placed atop that red arch.  
   – An orange wedge “roof” alongside the arch on the same level.  
 • A third orange cylinder is stacked on top of the left cylinder, making a taller column, which has a second orange wedge on its very top (another “roof”).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING BLOCKS FROM THE DICTIONARY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Matching each piece (without re‐orienting any block differently than shown) leads to the following dictionary‐indices:

LEFT TOWER
 • Top red arch  →  Index 3  
 • Bottom red arch  →  Index 3  (again)  
 • Two green bars  →  Index 4  (twice)  
 • Two yellow half‐cylinders → Index 12  (twice)  

RIGHT TOWER
 • Three orange cylinders (the two “legs” + one extra stacked) → Index 10  (three times)  
 • One horizontal yellow “bridge” block → Index 7  
 • One red arch on the bridge → Index 1  
 • One yellow half‐cylinder atop that arch → Index 12  
 • Two orange wedges (one over the arch level, one on top of the tall cylinder) → Index 16  (twice)

──────────────
LIST OF INDICES:
──────────────
 • #1 : 1×  
 • #3 : 2×  
 • #4 : 2×  
 • #7 : 1×  
 • #10: 3×  
 • #12: 3×  (2 for the left tower + 1 for the right)  
 • #16: 2×  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below is one possible sequence (you can of course rearrange it so long as the final stacking is the same):

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 3   // Bottom red arch of LEFT tower
  Step2:  Move block with index 4   // Lower green layer (LEFT)
  Step3:  Move block with index 12  // First yellow half-cylinder (LEFT)
  Step4:  Move block with index 12  // Second yellow half-cylinder (LEFT)
  Step5:  Move block with index 4   // Upper green layer (LEFT)
  Step6:  Move block with index 3   // Top red arch (LEFT tower complete)

  Step7:  Move block with index 10  // First orange cylinder (RIGHT base)
  Step8:  Move block with index 10  // Second orange cylinder (RIGHT base)
  Step9:  Move block with index 7   // Yellow bridge across both cylinders
  Step10: Move block with index 10  // Third orange cylinder stacked on left
  Step11: Move block with index 1   // Red arch on the yellow bridge
  Step12: Move block with index 12  // Yellow half-cylinder atop red arch
  Step13: Move block with index 16  // Orange wedge “roof” on bridge level
  Step14: Move block with index 16  // Orange wedge on top of tall cylinder
}

All blocks are thereby placed exactly as in the target image, using the given dictionary orientations without rotation.
